                        <strong>  

                                <font face="Arial" size="2">30-09-2017 :</font><font face="Arial" color="#0000FF" size="2">  CMD BSNL meeting with BSNL Unions and Associations Core Group: On behalf of NFTE BSNL Com. C. Singh G.S. along with GS of BSNLEU, GS AIBSNLEA and GS SNEA has attended the meeting convened by CMD BSNL today at 1530 hrs to discuss the present condition of BSNL. CMD apprised about the Indian Mobile congress (IMC) on 25-26 September 2017 at Pragati Maidan wherein many private operators CEOs visited BSNL . Best stall there is of BSNL. Current market scenario CMD informed that positive side for BSNL is that the market share of BSNL has increased from 8.6 in March,2017 to 8.84 in July 2017 in mobile segment despite of tough competition. Media has also reported that BSNL has challenge the Reliance Jio in the ongoing tariff war. Whole credit goes to the BSNL employees and we are proud of it. However BSNL has suffered on financial front. Revenue in July impacted huge due to GST implementation. In the month of Aug the realisation was 98.9% and in September till date 55%. Due to this cash crunch in the month of July the salary was disbursed on OD. Earlier IUC charges benchmark was 0.14 paisa which is now reduce to 0.6 paisa. In our opinion it should be minimum 0.22 paisa. Now BSNL has to launch aggressive tariffs in view of this BSNL in collaboration with micromax is launching bundled feature phone having Smartphone features on the price of Rs 2,200 and Rupees 97 sim with unlimited voice and Data. It will be matching brand with Jio. This product will save customers in rural and medium class. BSNL is subsidising Rs 1200 out of 2200 and this product will be named Bharat-1. BSNL has also tied up with Vodafone on prepaid service for free roaming now customer of BSNL may roam on Vodafone network freely . post-paid will also take place soon. Recently BSNL has received Rs 1500 crores from NFS amount which will help immediately. Further any suggestion may be given by unions and association within one week time in this regard. BSNL has also applied for 4G spectrum allocation (2100 MHz band) which will cater 3G also. The spectrum charges will be paid on yearly basis up to ten years. 2G phase VIII order need to be reviewed. 3rd PRC implementation in BSNL with 15 % fitment benefit: CMD informed that BSNL MC has approved the 3rd PRC report with 15% fitment benefit and it has been sent to DOT for clearance. Simultaneously it will be placed in the next Board meeting for approval shortly. He further mentioned that Secretary Telecom also commented that BSNL deserves for 3rd PRC implementation and she will meet Hon’ble MOSC(I/C) along with CMD BSNL in the next week to get his consent. He also mentioned that Hon’ble MOSC (I/C) wants to implement 3rd PRC in BSNL from his core of heart. CMD also shared his views in respect of subsidiary tower company. Before end of the meeting leaders requested for payment of PLI before Diwali. Hon. CMD assured to look into the issue.   
 
  
    
                           
                        
